name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Contributions from netizens
On March 30, in Shenyang Wanda, a couple cried on the street about their experiences.
It is reported that they saved 70,000 yuan and rented an outdoor shop to start a business. However, they did not open the business for a day and were told that the shop would be demolished during the renovation. During the demolition process, Wanda continued to attract investment.
The couple tried calling the police for help, but received no response.
According to a public document released by the Liaoning Provincial Government on March 15, Shenyang City is currently actively building a national civilized city. This year’s slogan is: “Make the people’s happiness more secure and sustainable.”

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Feng Jie issued another statement today, responding to the two accounts that are impersonating her on Twitter, and said that she has been hurt a lot on the Internet for so many years, so she doesn't want to show up on the Internet, and she just wants to live like an ordinary person. She also said that she doesn't like the content of the impersonator. She believes that if the impersonator wants to exercise the right to freedom of speech, he should use his own identity, his own name and his own photo to express his own opinions, instead of impersonating others. Impersonators should not express their own opinions while causing trouble to the person being impersonated.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Here I want to say that if you think that in this matter, saying what you want to hear is more important than impersonating someone else, then you might as well lend your own photo and name to this person instead of condoning him to impersonate someone else.
After all, "telling the truth" is the most important thing for you, so it shouldn't matter if your identity is used by those who tell the truth.
